For 6 and 15 (gcd 3), the Frobenius number is \( 1 \times 3 = 3 \). 3. For 10 and 15 (gcd 5), the Frobenius number is \( 1 \times 5 = 5 \). The largest Frobenius number among these pairs is 14, but we need to verify if 14 can be formed with all three coins. Since 14 cannot be formed using 6, 10, and 15, we check numbers sequentially starting from 14 upwards.
